A South West group has called on Vice President Yemi Osinbajo to answer the calls of Nigerians and declare his intention to run in the 2023 presidential race. Members of the political group are drawn from all South West states under the aegis of Osinbajo Southwest Group (OSG) and spoke during its official launch in Abeokuta, Ogun State. FG to deworm ten million pupils nationwide 10 dangerous criminal spots to be wary of in Abuja, Lagos Speaking on behalf of the group, the Coordinator of OSG in Osun State, Oyewale Olumuyiwa, said members of the group have analysed the capacity, experience and potentials of the presidential aspirants before zeroing on Osinbajo. Similarly, youth, professional bodies, entrepreneurs, farmers and artisans and other stakeholders under the umbrella of Movement for Better Nigeria (MFBN), Nasarawa State chapter, have endorsed Osinbajo. Speaking at a press conference in Lafia, the coordinator of MFBN, Dr Douglas Agbotu Akuba, said the emergence of the vice president would bring about continuity to finish the work of President Muhammadu Buhari.